        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See letters from T. H. Farrer, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6178.xml" resp="#automat">17 May 1868</ref> and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6183.xml" resp="#automat">18 May 1868</ref>, and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6185.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to T. H. Farrer, 19 May [1868]</ref>. CD refers to <hi rend="italic">Ophrys muscifera</hi> (<hi rend="italic">O. muscifera</hi> is a synonym of <hi rend="italic">O. insectifera</hi> subsp. <hi rend="italic">insectifera</hi>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6229.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from T. H. Farrer, 4 June 1868</ref>. CD refers to <hi rend="italic">Habenaria viridis</hi> (<hi rend="italic">H. viridis</hi> is a synonym of <hi rend="italic">Dactylorhiza viridis</hi>, the frog orchis.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6229.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from T. H. Farrer, 4 June 1868</ref>. CD refers to <hi rend="italic">Listera ovata</hi>; see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6010.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Orchids</hi></ref>, pp. 139–47.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2486.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Thomas Henry Huxley</ref> may have made this remark in a letter to CD that has not been found, or during his visit to Down House on 13 October 1861 (<ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin’s</ref> diary (DAR 242)); for CD’s response to Huxley’s scepticism, see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 9, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3293.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to T. H. Huxley, 22 October [1861]</ref>. For CD’s discussion of the mechanism for ejecting the pollinia of <hi rend="italic">Catasetum</hi>, see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6010.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Orchids</hi></ref>, pp. 212–48.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">There is no mention of an accompanying specimen in the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6229.xml" resp="#automat" cert="medium">letter from Farrer of 4 June 1868</ref>.</note>
